WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Wilinx' is a Workbench game which is a variation of the typical
'sliding-tiles-puzzle' type of game. A coloured 'wire' is located
at the upper left of a 7 by 7 spaces board. That wire is made up
of 7 small tiles that are linked together and these tiles cannot
be separated. The goal is to move the wire, piece by piece, from
its starting position, towards a 'receiving area' located at the
lower right position of the board. The least amount of moves it
takes to complete the game, the better it is...

  To complicate matters a bit, there are some 'neutral tiles' that
have to be moved eleswhere so that a part of the wire can move.
Additionally, keep in mind that none of the links of the wire can
be 'stretched' by more than one unit...

  All parts of the wire or a neutral tile can move anywhere on the
board either horizontally, vertically or diagonally. The neutral
tiles can 'wraparound' from one edge to the other opposing edge of
the board, but obviously none of the wire parts can do so...

  Have fun!

